text: Ivey-Ellington House is a historic home located at Cary, Wake County, North Carolina. The house was built about 1870, and is a 1 1/2-story, "T"-plan, frame I-house with board-and-batten siding. It has a steeply pitched roof, decorative scalloped gable trim, and pointed-arch windows. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 2008. ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in North Carolina Category:Gothic Revival architecture in North Carolina Category:Houses completed in 1870 Category:Houses in Wake County, North Carolina Category:National Register of Historic Places in Wake County, North Carolina
title: Ivey-Ellington House
